Aida is Ahmed’s mother’s sister. Aida finds herself in a disastrous marriage, though her father won’t allow her to divorce. Depressed and hopeless, Aida begins to take pills. Her husband arranged for her to get electroshock treatments, but nothing helps her. Aida finally resorts to suicide. To Ahmed, Aida’s story represents a cautionary tale of what can happen to women in a rigid, patriarchal society.